<div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
        <p class="section-label reveal">
            Pricing
        </p>
        <h1 class="reveal">
            Free to use.<br>
            <em>Pay only for power.</em>
        </h1>
        <p class="reveal">
            The everyday app is free forever, with no account and nothing leaving your phone.
            You pay only if you want the power features, and only when you reach for them.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- ── Why free works ── -->
<section>
    <div class="container">
        <p class="section-label reveal">
            How the <span class="tier">FREE</span> tier works
        </p>
        <p class="section-lead reveal">
            <span class="tier">FREE</span> is not a trial.
            It is the whole everyday app, and it stays free.
            You get the full capture-and-retrieve loop with no limit on retrieves, and the everyday cues used one at a time:
            a date or time, opening the app, an NFC tag tap, and a Wi-Fi network.
            Two of those carry a friendly limit, up to five tags and two Wi-Fi networks, counted as tags, not captures, so one
            tag holds as many reminders as you like.
            A grandparent with tags on the medicine cabinet and the kitchen, wake and bedtime reminders set by time, and the
            home and clubhouse on Wi-Fi lives here happily and never pays, which is exactly the intent.
        </p>
        <p class="section-lead reveal">
            Payment is for power and breadth, never for the basic act of remembering.
            Nothing you have captured is ever walled off, on any tier.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

