<!-- ── Solo explained ── -->
<section>
    <div class="container">
        <p class="section-label reveal">
            <span class="tier">SOLO</span> – $9.99, once
        </p>
        <h2 class="reveal">
            One purchase.<br>
            <em>No ongoing relationship.</em>
        </h2>
        <p class="section-lead reveal">
            <span class="tier">SOLO</span> unlocks the power features: the rest of the cues (location, charger, Focus, and
            Bluetooth), combining cues with conditions and delays, and unlimited tags and Wi-Fi networks.
            Everything still lives on your device.
            No account.
            No server.
            No subscription.
            Pay once and it's yours as long as you have the phone.
        </p>
        <p class="section-lead reveal">
            The prompt to buy appears at the right moment, when you reach for a paid cue, a sixth tag or third network, or
            your first combined cue.
            By then you already know what the app does for you, so you know exactly what you're paying for.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ── Connected explained ── -->
<section>
    <div class="container">
        <p class="section-label reveal">
            <span class="tier">CONNECTED</span> – $2.99/month or $24.99/year
        </p>
        <h2 class="reveal">
            Everything in <span class="tier">SOLO</span>,<br>
            <em>plus the people you trust.</em>
        </h2>
        <p class="section-lead reveal">
            <span class="tier">CONNECTED</span> adds a backend that routes captures, presence events, and context between
            people who have chosen to share, and it includes the <span class="tier">SOLO</span> power features.
            That backend has real ongoing costs: server infrastructure, encrypted relay, and push notification routing.
            A subscription is the honest pricing model for an ongoing cost.
            <span class="tier">SOLO</span> has none of those costs, which is why it's a one-time purchase.
        </p>
        <div class="cue-cards" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">

            <div class="cue-card reveal">
                <h3>
                    Shared captures
                </h3>
                <p>
                    Forward a capture to someone you're connected with.
                    They receive it with whatever cue you set – it finds them when it's actionable,
                    not when you sent it.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cue-card reveal">
                <h3>
                    Presence events
                </h3>
                <p>
                    NFC tag taps that signal your connected people – left home at 10:47 AM,
                    returned at 1:23 PM.
                    A presence log, not a tracker.
                    <a href="/caregivers" style="color: var(--accent);">See the caregiver use case →</a>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cue-card reveal">
                <h3>
                    Voice cue input
                </h3>
                <p>
                    Set a cue by speaking it.
                    "When I leave the house" resolves to a geofence departure on your saved home location.
                    Named locations you haven't defined yet prompt you to identify them – by Wi-Fi, map,
                    or NFC tag.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class="pricing-note reveal" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
            One subscription covers up to five family members through Family Sharing, so a parent and an adult child connect
            under a single payment.
            If you ever stop your subscription, everything you've unlocked stays yours.
            <span class="tier">CONNECTED</span> features pause.
            Everything else continues.
            After any 12 consecutive months of <span class="tier">CONNECTED</span>, the <span class="tier">SOLO</span> power
            features are yours permanently, automatically, no action required.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ── Supporter ── -->
<section>
    <div class="container">
        <p class="section-label reveal">
            Optional <span class="tier">SUPPORTER</span>
        </p>
        <h2 class="reveal">
            If it helps you,<br>
            <em>you can chip in.</em>
        </h2>
        <p class="section-lead reveal">
            A <span class="tier">SUPPORTER</span> purchase is entirely optional, for people who are happy on the free tier and
            want to give something back, or who want to support development beyond what they've paid.
            It unlocks nothing functional, only a small thank-you: a supporter badge, an alternate app icon, and a line in the
            about screen.
            It comes at a few price points so you can give what feels right.
            Nobody is ever asked to choose between paying and keeping a thought they captured.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ── FAQ ── -->
<section>
    <div class="container">
        <p class="section-label reveal">
            Pricing questions
        </p>
        <div class="faq-list">
            <div class="faq-item reveal">
                <p class="faq-q">
                    Can I try <span class="tier">CONNECTED</span> before committing to a year?
                </p>
                <p class="faq-a">
                    Yes – the monthly price is $2.99.
                    Start monthly, switch to annual whenever you're ready.
                    Annual is about 30% less than monthly over a year.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item reveal">
                <p class="faq-q">
                    What if I buy <span class="tier">SOLO</span> and later want <span class="tier">CONNECTED</span>?
                </p>
                <p class="faq-a">
                    You can upgrade to <span class="tier">CONNECTED</span> at any time.
                    <span class="tier">CONNECTED</span> includes the <span class="tier">SOLO</span> power features, and your
                    one-time <span class="tier">SOLO</span> purchase is what you fall back to if you ever cancel.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item reveal">
                <p class="faq-q">
                    Does the caregiver need their own subscription?
                </p>
                <p class="faq-a">
                    No.
                    One <span class="tier">CONNECTED</span> subscription covers up to five family members through Family
                    Sharing, so only one of you pays.
                    You each have your own private account for the connection itself, and both of you get the full app, not a
                    stripped-down companion version.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item reveal">
                <p class="faq-q">
                    What happens if I delete and reinstall the app?
                </p>
                <p class="faq-a">
                    The free everyday app has no limit to reset, so there is nothing to lose on the free tier except your local
                    captures, which is why you should back up your phone.
                    If you've purchased <span class="tier">SOLO</span> or subscribed to <span class="tier">CONNECTED</span>,
                    your purchase is restored through the App Store or Google Play restore mechanism.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
